## 1. Proposal Summary  
This proposal initiates a **comprehensive review and optimization** of the $CNET token distribution structure to ensure alignment with CampusNetDAO‚Äôs long-term governance and community growth objectives.

---

## 2. Motivation  
The current token allocation (100,000,000 CNET on Solana Devnet) served as a proof-of-concept phase.  
As the DAO transitions toward mainnet and real-world operations, it‚Äôs critical to rebalance allocations between governance, community rewards, partnerships, and the treasury.  

This review ensures:
- Governance power remains decentralized.  
- Long-term sustainability of incentive programs.  
- Transparent, fair token vesting for contributors.

---

## 3. Proposed Action Plan  

| Step | Description | Responsible Unit | Duration |
|------|--------------|------------------|-----------|
| 1 | Conduct full audit of existing token distribution and usage | Governance Circle | 1 week |
| 2 | Collect feedback from all DAO circles on allocation needs | All Circles | 1 week |
| 3 | Draft and publish new tokenomics framework | Treasury & Governance Circles | 2 weeks |
| 4 | Community voting on updated allocation | Governance Circle | 3 days |
| 5 | Implement new distribution parameters on-chain (Devnet ‚Üí Mainnet) | Core Devs | 1 week |

---

## 4. Budget & Token Allocation  

| Category | Amount (CNET) | Notes |
|-----------|---------------|-------|
| Governance Operations | 5,000 | Coordination, auditing, and documentation |
| Technical Audit Bounty | 7,000 | For community-led tokenomics review |
| Community Feedback Incentives | 3,000 | Reward DAO members contributing ideas |
| Publication & Transparency Costs | 2,000 | Dashboard + public record updates |
| **Total** | **17,000 CNET** | Governance Review Budget |

---

## 5. Expected Outcomes & KPIs  
- New tokenomics model with clear allocations and vesting schedules.  
- Minimum 20 active members contribute governance feedback.  
- Transparent DAO token dashboard published on GitHub.  
- Increased voter participation (‚â•25% of circulating CNET).  

---

## 6. Governance Impact  
This proposal enhances DAO legitimacy by aligning token governance with real participation rather than central control.  
It reaffirms CampusNetDAO‚Äôs founding value ‚Äî **students govern, not gatekeepers**.  
Oversight: **Governance Circle**, validated by **Core Contributors**.

---

## 7. Voting Parameters  

| Parameter | Value |
|------------|--------|
| Voting Platform | Snapshot / Discord Poll |
| Minimum Quorum | 20% of circulating CNET |
| Required Approval | 66% majority |
| Voting Duration | 96 hours |

---

## 8. Implementation Plan  
Upon approval, the Governance Circle will execute a phased rollout of the new distribution framework.  
All adjustments and vesting logs will be made public in the DAO changelog.  
Final mainnet token migration will only occur after the DAO-wide vote confirms readiness.

